	[em 
		"R.C. Pro-Am II
	]em
	" is the sequel to 
	[em 
		"R.C. Pro-Am
	]em
	" by Rare. The biggest addition to the game is multiplayer, allowing up to four players to race against each other with the use of the NES Four Score accessory. Another difference is that instead of power-ups and weapons you can pick up on the track, you pick up money that can be used to purchase power-ups at a store in-between races. However, you can still collect rare letters that can spell out a word that can give you power-ups.
	$LF
]div
